      "message": "No trailing semicolon. The whole “do {} while (false)” construct is supposed to make sure that the whole macro is treated at the point of use the same way that a function call would with respect to things like semicolons and braces, and you’ve got the requirement to write the semicolon at the point of use, just like you would with a function call. If you include a semicolon in the macro, that breaks. Same in SET_GPRS64().",
