      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-07-28T15:55:49Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "It turns out that\u0027s just glibc\u0027s view of it. The kernel uses the extra status word at the end of the SignalFloatContext32 to indicate whether there\u0027s an fxsave following. Similarly, the SignalFloatContext64 may actually be an xsave.",
